PURPORTK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and the Supreme Personality of Godhead are identical. Therefore Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is referred to as \xc3\x92Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n\xc3\x93 throughout the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n is the ultimate in the Absolute Truth. Absolute Truth is realized in three phases of understanding, namely Brahman or the impersonal all-pervasive spirit; \nParam\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, or the localized aspect of the Supreme within the heart of all living entities; and Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n, or the Supreme Personality of Godhead, Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. In the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam this conception of the Absolute Truth is explained thus:vadanti tat tattva-vidas tattva\xe2\x80\xb9 yaj j\xc5\x81\xe2\x88\x92nam advayambrahmeti param\xe2\x88\x92tmeti bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n iti \xe2\x80\x9cabdyate.\xc3\x92The Absolute Truth is realized in three phases of understanding by the knower of the Absolute Truth, and all of them are identical. Such phases of the Absolute Truth are expressed as Brahman, Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, and Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n.\xc3\x93 (Bh\xe2\x88\x92g. 1.2.11) These three divine aspects can be explained by the example of the sun, which also has three different aspects, namely the sunshine, the sun\xc3\x95s surface and the sun planet itself. One who studies the sunshine only is the preliminary student. One who understands the sun\xc3\x95s surface is further advanced. And one who can enter into the sun planet is the highest. Ordinary students who are satisfied by simply understanding the sunshine\xc3\x91its universal pervasiveness and the glaring effulgence of its impersonal nature\xc3\x91may be compared to those who can \nrealize only the Brahman feature of the Absolute Truth. The student who has '
b'advanced still further can know the sun disc, which is compared to knowledge of the Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92 feature of the Absolute Truth. And the student who can enter into the heart of the sun planet is compared to those who realize the personal features of the Supreme Absolute Truth. Therefore, the bhaktas, or the transcendentalists who have realized the Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n feature of the Absolute \nTruth, are the topmost transcendentalists, although all students who are engaged in the study of the Absolute Truth are engaged in the same subject matter. The sunshine, the sun disc and the inner affairs of the sun planet \ncannot be separated from one another, and yet the students of the three different phases are not in the same category.The Sanskrit word Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n is explained by the great authority, Par\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9cara Muni, the father of Vy\xe2\x88\x92sadeva. The Supreme Personality who possesses all riches, all strength, all fame, all beauty, all knowledge and all renunciation is called Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n. There are many persons who are very rich, very powerful, very beautiful, very famous, very learned, and very much detached, but no one \ncan claim that he possesses all riches, all strength, etc., entirely. Only K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa can claim this because He is the Supreme Personality of Godhead. No living entity, including Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, Lord \xe2\x80\xa1iva, or N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa, can possess opulences as fully as K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Therefore it is concluded in the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 by Lord Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 himself that Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead. No one is equal to or above Him. He is the primeval Lord, or Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n, known as Govinda, and He is the supreme cause of all causes.\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9cvara\xc5\xa1 parama\xc5\xa1 k\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc5\xa1 sac-cid-\xe2\x88\x92nanda-vigraha\xc5\xa1an\xe2\x88\x92dir \xe2\x88\x92dir govinda\xc5\xa1 sarua-k\xe2\x88\x92ra\xe2\x80\x9aa-k\xe2\x88\x92ra\xe2\x80\x9aam\xc3\x92There are many personalities possessing the qualities of Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n, but K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the supreme because none can excel Him. He is the Supreme Person, and His body is eternal, full of knowledge and bliss. He is the primeval Lord Govinda and the cause of all causes.\xc3\x93 (Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 5.1)In the Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam also there is a list of many incarnations of the Supreme Personality of Godhead, but K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is described as the original Personality of Godhead, from whom many, many incarnations and Personalities of Godhead expand:ete c\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\xb9\xe2\x80\x9ca-kal\xe2\x88\x92\xc5\xa1 pu\xe2\x80\xb9sa\xc5\xa1 k\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aas tu bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n svayamindr\xe2\x88\x92ri-vy\xe2\x88\x92kula\xe2\x80\xb9 loka\xe2\x80\xb9 m\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\xb8ayanti yuge yuge'
b'\xc3\x92All the lists of the incarnations of Godhead submitted herewith are either plenary expansions or parts of the plenary expansions of the Supreme Godhead, but K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead Himself.\xc3\x93 (Bhag. 1.3.28)Therefore, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the original Supreme Personality of Godhead, the Absolute Truth, the source of both the Supersoul and the impersonal Brahman.In the presence of the Supreme Personality of Godhead, Arjuna\xc3\x95s lamentation \nfor his kinsmen is certainly unbecoming, and therefore K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa expressed His surprise with the word kutas, \xc3\x92wherefrom.\xc3\x93 Such unmanly sentiments were never expected from a person belonging to the civilized class of men known as \xe2\x80\xa2ryans. The word \xe2\x88\x92ryan is applicable to persons who know the value of life and have a civilization based on spiritual realization. Persons who are led by the material conception of life do not know that the aim of life is realization of the Absolute Truth, Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, or Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n, and they are captivated by the \nexternal features of the material world, and therefore they do not know what liberation is. Persons who have no knowledge of liberation from material bondage are called non-\xe2\x80\xa2ryans. Although Arjuna was a k\xc5\x92atriya, he was deviating from his prescribed duties by declining to fight. This act of cowardice is described as befitting the non-\xe2\x80\xa2ryans. Such deviation from duty does not help one in the progress of spiritual life, nor does it even give one the opportunity to become famous in this world. Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa did not approve of \nthe so-called compassion of Arjuna for his kinsmen.
