I can find no means to drive away this grief which is drying up my senses. I will not be able to destroy it even if I win an unrivalled kingdom on the earth with \nsovereignty like the demigods in heaven.
PURPORTAlthough Arjuna was putting forward so many arguments based on knowledge of the principles of religion and moral codes, it appears that he was unable to solve his real problem without the help of the spiritual master, Lord \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. He could understand that his so-called knowledge was useless in driving away his problems, which were drying up his whole existence; and it was impossible for him to solve such perplexities without the help of a spiritual master like Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Academic knowledge, scholarship, high position, etc., \nare all useless in solving the problems of life; help can only be given by a spiritual master like K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Therefore, the conclusion is that a spiritual master who is one hundred percent K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious is the bona fide spiritual master, for he can solve the problems of life. Lord Caitanya said that one who is '
b'master in the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, regardless of his social position, is the real spiritual master.yei k\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa-tattva-vett\xe2\x88\x92, sei \xc3\x94guru\xc3\x95 haya.(Caitanya-carit\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9eta, Madhya 8.127)\xc3\x92It does not matter whether a person is a vipra [learned scholar in Vedic wisdom] or is born in a lower family, or is in the renounced order of life\xc3\x91if he \nis master in the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, he is the perfect and bona fide spiritual master.\xc3\x93 So without being a master in the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, no one is a bona fide spiritual master. It is also said in Vedic literatures:\xc5\x92a\xc4\xb1-karma-nipu\xe2\x80\x9ao vipro mantra-tantra-vi\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92rada\xc5\xa1avai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aavo gurur na sy\xe2\x88\x92d vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava\xc5\xa1 \xe2\x80\x9cvapaco guru\xc5\xa1\xc3\x92A scholarly br\xe2\x88\x92hma\xe2\x80\x9aa, expert in all subjects of Vedic knowledge, is unfit to become a spiritual master without being a Vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava, or expert in the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness. But a person born in a family of a lower caste can become a spiritual master if he is a Vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava, or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious.\xc3\x93The problems of material existence\xc3\x91birth, old age, disease and death\xc3\x91cannot be counteracted by accumulation of wealth and economic development. In many parts of the world there are states which are replete with all facilities of life, which are full of wealth, and economically developed, \nyet the problems of material existence are still present. They are seeking peace in different ways, but they ean achieve real happiness only if they consult K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, or the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam\xc3\x91which constitute the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x91or the bona fide representative of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the man in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness.If economic development and material comforts could drive away one\xc3\x95s lamentations for family, social, national or international inebrieties, then \nArjuna would not have said that even an unrivalled kingdom on earth or supremacy like that of the demigods in the heavenly planets would not be able to drive away his lamentations. He sought, therefore, refuge in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, and that is the right path for peace and harmony. Economic development or supremacy over the world can be finished at any moment by the cataclysms of material nature. Even elevation into a higher planetary '
b'situation, as men are now seeking a place on the moon planet, can also be finished at one stroke. The Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 confirms this: k\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9ae pu\xe2\x80\x9aye martyaloka\xe2\x80\xb9 vi\xe2\x80\x9canti \xc3\x92When the results of pious activities are finished, one falls down again from the peak of happiness to the lowest status of life.\xc3\x93 Many politicians of the world have fallen down in that way. Such downfalls only constitute more causes for lamentation.Therefore, if we want to curb lamentation for good, then we have to take shelter of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, as Arjuna is seeking to do. So Arjuna asked K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to solve his \nproblem definitely, and that is the way of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness.
