b'In the Vedas, in the Ka\xc4\xb1ha Upani\xc5\x92ad as well as in the \xe2\x80\xa1vet\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9cvatara Upani\xc5\x92ad, it is said that the Supreme Personality of Godhead is the maintainer of innumerable living entities, in terms of their different situations according to individual work and reaction of work. That Supreme Personality of Godhead is also, by His plenary portions, alive in the heart of every living entity. Only saintly persons who can see, within and without, the same Supreme Lord, can actually attain to perfect and eternal peace.nityo nity\xe2\x88\x92n\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\xb9 cetana\xe2\x80\x9c cetan\xe2\x88\x92n\xe2\x88\x92mtam \xe2\x88\x92tmastha\xe2\x80\xb9 ye \xc3\x95nupa\xe2\x80\x9cyanti dh\xe2\x80\x9dr\xe2\x88\x92ste\xc5\x92\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\xb9 \xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92nti\xc5\xa1 \xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9cvat\xe2\x80\x9d netare\xc5\x92\xe2\x88\x92m.(Ka\xc4\xb1ha 2.2.13)The same Vedic truth given to Arjuna is given to all persons in the world who pose themselves as very learned but factually have but a poor fund of knowledge. The Lord says clearly that He Himself, Arjuna, and all the kings who are assembled on the battlefield, are eternally individual beings and that the Lord is eternally the maintainer of the individual living entities both in \ntheir conditioned as well as in their liberated situations. The Supreme Personality of Godhead is the supreme individual person, and Arjuna, the Lord\xc3\x95s eternal associate, and all the kings assembled there are individual, eternal persons. It is not that they did not exist as individuals in the past, and it is not that they will not remain eternal persons. Their individuality existed in the past, and their individuality will continue in the future without interruption. Therefore, there is no cause for lamentation for anyone.The M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d theory that after liberation the individual soul, separated by the covering of m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92 or illusion, will merge into the impersonal Brahman and \nlose its individual existence is not supported herein by Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the supreme authority. Nor is the theory that we only think of individuality in the conditioned state supported herein. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa clearly says herein that in the future also the individuality of the Lord and others, as it is confirmed in the Upani\xc5\x92ads, will continue eternally. This statement of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is authoritative \nbecause K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa cannot be subject to illusion. If individuality is not a fact, then K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa would not have stressed it so much\xc3\x91even for the future. The M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d may argue that the individuality spoken of by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is not spiritual, but '
b'material. Even accepting the argument that the individuality is material, then how can one distinguish K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s individuality? K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa affirms His individuality in the past and confirms His individuality in the future also. He has confirmed His individuality in many ways, and impersonal Brahman has been declared to be subordinate to Him. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has maintained spiritual individuality all along; if He is accepted as an ordinary conditioned soul in individual consciousness, then His Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 has no value as authoritative scripture. A common man with all the four defects of human frailty is unable to teach that which is \nworth hearing. The G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 is above such literature. No mundane book compares with the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. When one accepts K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as an ordinary man, the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 loses all importance. The M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d argues that the plurality mentioned in this verse is conventional and that it refers to the body. But previous to this verse such a bodily conception is already condemned. After condemning the bodily conception of the living entities, how was it possible for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to place a conventional proposition on the body again? Therefore, individuality is \nmaintained on spiritual grounds and is thus confirmed by great \xe2\x88\x92c\xe2\x88\x92ryas like \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d R\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x88\x92nuja and others. It is clearly mentioned in many places in the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 that this spiritual individuality is understood by those who are devotees of the Lord. Those who are envious of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as the Supreme Personality of Godhead have no bona fide access to the great literature. The nondevotee\xc3\x95s approach to the teachings of the G\xe2\x80\x9dta is something like bees licking on a bottle of honey. One cannot have a taste of honey unless one opens the bottle. Similarly, the \nmysticism of the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 can be understood only by devotees, and no one else can taste it, as it is stated in the Fourth Chapter of the book. Nor can the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 be touched by persons who envy the very existence of the Lord. Therefore, the M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d explanation of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 is a most misleading presentation of the whole truth. Lord Caitanya has forbidden us to read commentations made by the M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9ds and warns that one who takes to such an understanding of the M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d philosophy loses all power to understand \nthe real mystery of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. If individuality refers to the empirical universe, then there is no need of teaching by the Lord. The plurality of the individual soul and of the Lord is an eternal fact, and it is confirmed by the Vedas as above mentioned.'
b'
