Be steadfast in yoga, O Arjuna. Perform your duty and abandon all attachment to success or failure. Such evenness of mind is called yoga.
PURPORTK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa tells Arjuna that he should act in yoga. And what is that yoga? Yoga means to concentrate the mind upon the Supreme by controlling the ever-disturbing senses. And who is the Supreme? The Supreme is the Lord. And because He Himself is telling Arjuna to fight, Arjuna has nothing to do with \nthe results of the fight. Gain or victory are K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s concern; Arjuna is simply advised to act according to the dictation of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. The following of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s dictation is real yoga, and this is practiced in the process called K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness. By K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness only can one give up the sense of proprietorship. One has to become the servant of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, or the servant of the servant of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. That is the right way to discharge duty in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, which alone can help one to act in yoga.\nArjuna is a k\xc5\x92atriya, and as such he is participating in the var\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9crama-dharma institution. It is said in the Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au Pura\xe2\x80\x9aa that in the var\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9crama-dharma, the whole aim is to satisfy Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au. No one should satisfy himself, as is the rule in the material world, but one should satisfy K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. So, unless one satisfies K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, one cannot correctly observe the principles of var\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9crama-dharma. Indirectly, Arjuna was advised to act as K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa told him.
