When your mind is no longer disturbed by the flowery language of the Vedas, and when it remains fixed in the trance of self-realization, then you will have attained the Divine consciousness.
PURPORTTo say that one is in sam\xe2\x88\x92dhi is to say that one has fully realized K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness; that is, one in full sam\xe2\x88\x92dhi has realized Brahman, Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92 and Bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n. The highest perfection of self-realization is to understand that one is eternally the servitor of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and that one\xc3\x95s only business is to \ndischarge one\xc3\x95s duties in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness. A K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious person, or unflinching devotee of the Lord, should not be disturbed by the flowery language of the Vedas nor be engaged in fruitive activities for promotion to the heavenly kingdom. In K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, one comes directly into communion with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and thus all directions from K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa may be understood in that transcendental state. One is sure to achieve results by such activities and attain conclusive knowledge. One has only to carry out the orders of \nK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa or His representative, the spiritual master.
