b'consciousness. One who is situated in this perfect stage knows that because K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the proprietor of everything, therefore everything must be used for the satisfaction of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Arjuna did not want to fight for his own sense satisfaction, but when he became fully K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious he fought because K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa wanted him to fight. For himself there was no desire to fight, but for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa the same Arjuna fought to his best ability. Desire for the satisfaction of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is really desirelessness; it is not an artificial attempt to abolish desires. The living entity cannot be desireless or senseless, but he does have to change \nthe quality of the desires. A materially desireless person certainly knows that everything belongs to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa (\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92syam ida\xe2\x80\xb9 sarvam), and therefore he does not falsely claim proprietorship over anything. This transcendental knowledge is based on self-realization\xc3\x91namely, knowing perfectly well that every living entity is the eternal part and parcel of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in spiritual identity. and therefore the eternal position of the living entity is never on the level of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa or greater than Him. This understanding of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness is the \nbasic principle of real peace.
