vad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 as the liberated stage. Therefore, br\xe2\x88\x92hm\xe2\x80\x9d-sthiti\xc5\xa1 is liberation from material bondage.\xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dla Bhaktivinode \xe2\x80\x93h\xe2\x88\x92kur has summarized this Second Chapter of the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 as being the contents for the whole text. In the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, the subject matters are karma-yoga, j\xc5\x81\xe2\x88\x92na-yoga, and bhakti-yoga. In the Second Chapter karma-yoga and j\xc5\x81\xe2\x88\x92na-yoga have been clearly discussed, and a glimpse of bhakti-yoga has also been given, as the contents for the complete text.Thus end the Bhaktivedanta Purports to the Second Chapter of the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 in the matter of its Contents.'
