rn order which is without consideration of so-\ncalled kinsmen in the bodily relationship, that reluctance should be thrown off; in this way one may become vigata-jvara, or without feverish mentality or lethargy. Everyone, according to his quality and position, has a particular type of work to discharge, and all such duties may be discharged in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, as described above. That will lead one to the path of liberation.'
