b'such knowledge and specific realization can be understood if it is explained by the Lord Himself." Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 gives us that knowledge, specifically knowledge of the self. The living entities are parts and parcels of the Lord, and therefore they are simply meant to serve the Lord. This consciousness is called K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness. So, from the very beginning of life one has to learn this K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, and thereby one may become fully K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious and act accordingly.Lust is only the perverted reflection of the love of God which is natural for \nevery living entity. But if one is educated in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness from the very beginning, that natural love of God cannot deteriorate into lust. When love of God deteriorates into lust, it is very difficult to return to the normal condition. Nonetheless, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness is so powerful that even a late beginner can become a lover of God by following the regulative principles of devotional service. So, from any stage of life, or from the time of understanding its urgency, one can begin regulating the senses in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa \nconsciousness, devotional service of the Lord, and turn the lust into love of Godhead!the highest perfectional stage of human life.
