b'the name Vaivasvata); pr\xe2\x88\x92ha\xc3\x91told; manu\xc5\xa1\xc3\x91the father of mankind; ik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92kave\xc3\x91unto King Ik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku; abrav\xe2\x80\x9dt\xc3\x91said.
TRANSLATION
The Blessed Lord said: I instructed this imperishable science of yoga to the sun-god, Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n, and Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n instructed it to Manu, the father of mankind, and Manu in turn instructed it to Ik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku.
PURPORTHerein we find the history of the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 traced from a remote time when it was delivered to the royal order, the kings of all planets. This science is especially meant for the protection of the inhabitants and therefore the royal order should understand it in order to be able to rule the citizens and protect them from the material bondage to lust. Human life is meant for cultivation of spiritual knowledge, in eternal relationship with the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and the executive heads of all states and all planets are obliged to impart this lesson to the citizens by education, culture and \ndevotion. In other words, the executive heads of all states are intended to spread the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness so that the people may take advantage of this great science and pursue a successful path, utilizing the opportunity of the human form of life.In this millennium, the sun-god is known as Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n, the king of the sun, which is the origin of all planets within the solar system. In the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 it is stated:yac-cak\xc5\x92ur e\xc5\x92a savit\xe2\x88\x92 sakala-grah\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\xb9yasy\xe2\x88\x92j\xc5\x81ay\xe2\x88\x92 bhramati sambh\xe2\x80\x9eta-k\xe2\x88\x92lacakrogovindam \xe2\x88\x92di-puru\xc5\x92a\xe2\x80\xb9 tam aha\xe2\x80\xb9 bhaj\xe2\x88\x92mi"Let me worship," Lord Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 said, "the Supreme Personality of Godhead, Govinda [K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa], who is the original person and under whose order the sun, which is the king of all planets, is assuming immense power and heat. The sun represents the eye of the Lord and traverses its orbit in obedience to His order."'
b'The sun is the king of the planets, and the sun-god (at present of the name Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n) rules the sun planet, which is controlling all other planets by supplying heat and light. He is rotating under the order of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa originally made Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n His first disciple to understand the science of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. The G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 is not, therefore, a speculative treatise for the insignificant mundane scholar but is a standard book of knowledge coming down from time immemorial. In the Mah\xe2\x88\x92bh\xe2\x88\x92rata (\xe2\x80\xa1\xe2\x88\x92nti-parva 348.51\xc3\x9052) we can trace out the history of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 as follows:tret\xe2\x88\x92-yug\xe2\x88\x92dau ca tato vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n manave dadaumanu\xe2\x80\x9c ca loka-bh\xe2\x80\x9ety-artha\xe2\x80\xb9 sut\xe2\x88\x92yek\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92kave dadauik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92 ca kathito vy\xe2\x88\x92pya lok\xe2\x88\x92n avasthit\xe2\x88\x92\xc5\xa1"In the beginning of the Tret\xe2\x88\x92-yuga [millennium] this science of the relationship with the Supreme was delivered by Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n to Manu. Manu, \nbeing the father of mankind, gave it to his son Mah\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ja Ik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku, the King of \nthis earth planet and forefather of the Raghu dynasty in which Lord R\xe2\x88\x92macandra appeared. Therefore, Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 existed in the human society from the time of Mah\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ja Ik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku."At the present moment we have just passed through five thousand years of the Kali-yuga, which lasts 432,000 years. Before this there was Dv\xe2\x88\x92para-yuga (800,000 years), and before that there was Tret\xe2\x88\x92-yuga (1,200,000 years). Thus, some 2,005,000 years ago, Manu spoke the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 to his disciple and \nson Mah\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ja lk\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku, the King of this planet earth. The age of the current Manu is calculated to last some 305,300,000 years, of which 120,400,000 have passed. Accepting that before the birth of Manu, the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 was spoken by the Lord to His disciple, the sun-god Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n, a rough estimate is that the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 was spoken at least 120,400,000 years ago; and in human society it has been \nextant for two million years. It was respoken by the Lord again to Arjuna about five thousand years ago. That is the rough estimate of the history of the \nG\xe2\x80\x9dta, according to the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 itself and according to the version of the speaker, Lord \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. It was spoken to the sun-god Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n because he is also a k\xc5\x92atriya and is the father of all k\xc5\x92atriyas who are descendants of the sun-god, or the Because Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 is as good as the Vedas, being spoken by the Supreme Personality of Godhead, this knowledge is apauru\xc5\x92eya, superhuman. Since the Vedic instructions are accepted as they are, without human interpretation, the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 must therefore be accepted '
b'without mundane interpretation. The mundane wranglers may speculate on the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 in their own ways, but that is not Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 as it is. Therefore, Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 has to be accepted as it is, from the disciplic succession, and it is described herein that the Lord spoke to the sun-god, the sun-god spoke to his son Manu, and Manu spoke to his son Ik\xc5\x92v\xe2\x88\x92ku.
