TRANSLATION
Arjuna said: The sun-god Vivasv\xe2\x88\x92n is senior by birth to You. How am I to understand that in the beginning You instructed this science to him?'
b'
PURPORTArjuna is an accepted devotee of the Lord, so how could he not believe K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s words? The fact is that Arjuna is not inquiring for himself but for those who do not believe in the Supreme Personality of Godhead or for the demons who do not like the idea that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa should be accepted as the Supreme Personality of Godhead; for them only Arjuna inquires on this point, as if he were himself not aware of the Personality of Godhead, or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. As it will be evident from the Tenth Chapter, Arjuna knew perfectly well that \nK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead, the fountainhead of everything and the last word in Transcendence. Of course, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa also appeared as the son of Devak\xe2\x80\x9d on this earth. How K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa remained the same Supreme Personality of Godhead, the eternal, original person, is very difficult for an ordinary man to understand. Therefore, to clarify this point, Arjuna put this question before K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa so that He Himself could speak authoritatively. That K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the supreme authority is accepted by the whole world, not only at present, but \nfrom time immemorial, and the demons alone reject Him. Anyway, since K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the authority accepted by all, Arjuna put this question before Him in order that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa would describe Himself without being depicted by the demons who always try to distort Him in a way understandable to the demons and their followers. It is necessary that everyone, for his own interest, know the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Therefore, when K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa Himself speaks about Himself, it is auspicious for all the worlds. To the demons, such explanations by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa \nHimself may appear to be strange because the demons always study K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa from their own standpoint, but those who are devotees heartily welcome the statements of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa when they are spoken by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa Himself. The devotees will always worship such authoritative statements of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa because they are always eager to know more and more about Him. The atheists, who consider K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa an ordinary man, may in this way come to know that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is superhuman, that He is sac-cid-\xe2\x88\x92nanda-vigraha\xc3\x91the eternal form of bliss and \nknowledge\xc3\x91that He is transcendental, and that He is above the domination of the modes of material nature and above the influence of time and space. A devotee of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s, like Arjuna, is undoubtedly above any misunderstanding of the transcendental position of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Arjuna\xc3\x95s putting this question before the Lord is simply an attempt by the devotee to defy the atheistic attitude of '
b'persons who consider K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to be an ordinary human being subject to the modes of material nature.
