ection of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, all attempts remain imperfect, as is stated in the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam:ak\xe2\x88\x92ma\xc5\xa1 sarva-k\xe2\x88\x92mo v\xe2\x88\x92 mok\xc5\x92a-k\xe2\x88\x92ma ud\xe2\x88\x92radh\xe2\x80\x9d\xc5\xa1t\xe2\x80\x9dvre\xe2\x80\x9aa bhakti-yogena yajeta puru\xc5\x92a\xe2\x80\xb9 param"Whether one is without desire [the condition of the devotees], or is desirous of all fruitive results, or is after liberation, one should with all efforts \ntry to worship the Supreme Personality of Godhead for complete perfection, culminating in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness." (Bh\xe2\x88\x92g. 2.3.10)'
