PURPORTThere is a great misconception about the gods or demigods of this material world, and men of less intelligence, although passing as great scholars, take these demigods to be various forms of the Supreme Lord. Actually, the demigods are not different forms of God, but they are God\xc3\x95s different parts and parcels. God is one, and the parts and parcels are many. The Vedas say, nityo nity\xe2\x88\x92n\xe2\x88\x92m: God is one. \xe2\x80\xa6\xe2\x80\x9cvara\xc5\xa1 parama\xc5\xa1 k\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc5\xa1. The Supreme God is one\n\xc3\x91K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x91and the demigods are delegated with powers to manage this material world. These demigods are all living entities (nity\xe2\x88\x92n\xe2\x88\x92m) with \ndifferent grades of material power. They cannot be equal to the Supreme God\xc3\x91N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa, Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Anyone who thinks that God and the demigods are on the same level is called an atheist, or p\xe2\x88\x92\xc5\x92a\xe2\x80\x9a\xc5\xb8\xe2\x80\x9d. Even the great demigods like Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1iva cannot be compared to the Supreme Lord. In fact, the Lord is worshiped by demigods such as Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1iva (\xe2\x80\x9civa-viri\xc5\x81ci-nutam). '
