PURPORTThese sacrifices may be fitted into various divisions. There are persons who are sacrificing their possessions in the form of various kinds of charities. In India, the rich mercantile community or princely orders open various kinds of charitable institutions like dharma\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92l\xe2\x88\x92, anna-k\xc5\x92etra, atithi-\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92l\xe2\x88\x92, anathalaya, vidy\xe2\x88\x92p\xe2\x80\x9d\xc4\xb1ha, etc. In other countries, too, there are many hospitals, old age homes and similar charitable foundations meant for distributing food, education and \nmedical treatment free to the poor. All these charitable activities are called dravyamaya-yaj\xc5\x81a. There are others who, for higher elevation in life or for promotion to higher planets within the universe, voluntarily accept many kinds of austerities such as candr\xe2\x88\x92yana and c\xe2\x88\x92turm\xe2\x88\x92sya. These processes entail severe vows for conducting life under certain rigid rules. For example, under the c\xe2\x88\x92turm\xe2\x88\x92sya vow the candidate does not shave for four months during the year (July to October), he does not eat certain foods, does not eat twice in a \nday and does not leave home. Such sacrifice of the comforts of life is called tapomaya-yaj\xc5\x81a. There are still others who engage themselves in different kinds of mystic yogas like the Pata\xc5\x81jali system (for merging into the existence of the Absolute), or ha\xc4\xb1ha-yoga or a\xc5\x92\xc4\xb1\xe2\x88\x92\xef\xac\x81ga-yoga (for particular perfections). And some travel to all the sanctified places of pilgrimage. All these practices are called yoga-yaj\xc5\x81a, sacrifice for a certain type of perfection in the material world. There are others who engage themselves in the studies of different \nVedic literatures, specifically the Upani\xc5\x92ads and or the s\xe2\x88\x92\xef\xac\x81khya philosophy. All of these are called sv\xe2\x88\x92dhy\xe2\x88\x92ya-yaj\xc5\x81a, or engagement in the sacrifice of studies. All these yog\xe2\x80\x9ds are faithfully engaged in different types of sacrifice and are seeking a higher status of life. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, is, however, different from these because it is the direct service of the Supreme Lord. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness cannot be attained by any one of the above-mentioned types of sacrifices but can be attained only by the mercy of the '
b'Lord and His bona fide devotee. Therefore, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness is transcendental.
