b'controlling the senses and for advancement in spiritual realization. This practice involves controlling the air within the body to enable simultaneous passage in opposite directions. The ap\xe2\x88\x92na air goes downward, and the pr\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa air goes up. The pr\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92ma yog\xe2\x80\x9d practices breathing the opposite way until the currents are neutralized into equilibrium. Similarly, when the exhaled breathing is offered to inhaled breathing, it is called recaka. When both air currents are completely stopped, it is called kumbhaka-yoga. By practice of kumbhaka-yoga, the yog\xe2\x80\x9ds increase the duration of life by many, many years. A \nK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious person, however, being always situated in the transcendental loving service of the Lord, automatically becomes the controller of the senses. His senses, being always engaged in the service of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, have no chance of becoming otherwise engaged. So at the end of life, he is naturally transferred to the transcendental plane of Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; consequently he makes no attempt to increase his longevity. He is at once raised to the platform of liberation. A K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious person begins from the transcendental stage, and he is \nconstantly in that consciousness. Therefore, there is no falling down, and ultimately he enters into the abode of the Lord without delay. The practice of reduced eating is automatically done when one eats only K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa pras\xe2\x88\x92dam, or food which is offered first to the Lord. Reducing the eating process is very \nhelpful in the matter of sense control. And without sense control there is no possibility of getting out of the material entanglement.
