The Blessed Lord said: One who is unattached to the fruits of his work and who works as he is obligated is in the renounced order of life, and he is the true mystic: not he who lights no fire and performs no work.
PURPORTIn this chapter the Lord explains that the process of the eightfold yoga system is a means to control the mind and the senses. However, this is very difficult for people in general to perform, especially in the age of Kali. Although the eightfold yoga system is recommended in this chapter, the Lord emphasizes that the process of karma-yoga, or acting in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, is better. Everyone acts in this world to maintain his family and their \nparaphernalia, but no one is working without some self-interest, some personal gratification, be it concentrated or extended. The criterion of perfection is to act in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, and not with a view to enjoying the fruits of work. To act in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness is the duty of every living entity because all are constitutionally parts and parcels of the Supreme. The parts of the body work for the satisfaction of the whole body. The limbs of the body do not act for self-satisfaction but for the satisfaction of the complete whole. Similarly, the \nliving entity who acts for satisfaction of the supreme whole and not for personal satisfaction is the perfect sanny\xe2\x88\x92s\xe2\x80\x9d, the perfect yog\xe2\x80\x9d.The sanny\xe2\x88\x92s\xe2\x80\x9ds sometimes artificially think that they have become liberated from all material duties, and therefore they cease to perform agnihotra yaj\xc5\x81as (fire sacrifices), but actually they are self-interested because their goal is \nbecoming one with the impersonal Brahman. Such a desire is greater than any material desire, but it is not without self-interest. Similarly, the mystic yog\xe2\x80\x9d who practices the yoga system with half-open eyes, ceasing all material activities, desires some satisfaction for his personal self. But a person acting in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness works for the satisfaction of the whole, without self-interest. A K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\x