PURPORT"Sacred place" refers to places of pilgrimage. In India the yog\xe2\x80\x9ds, the transcendentalists or the devotees all leave home and reside in sacred places such as Pray\xe2\x88\x92g, Mathur\xe2\x88\x92, V\xe2\x80\x9end\xe2\x88\x92vana, H\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9dke\xe2\x80\x9ca, and Hardwar and in solitude practice yoga where the sacred rivers like the Yamun\xe2\x88\x92 and the Ganges flow. But often this is not possible, especially for Westerners. The so-called yoga societies in big cities may be successful in earning material benefit, but they \nare not at all suitable for the actual practice of yoga. One who is not self-controlled and whose mind is not undisturbed cannot practice meditation. Therefore, in the B\xe2\x80\x9ehan-N\xe2\x88\x92rad\xe2\x80\x9dya Pur\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa it is said that in the Kali-yuga (the '
b'present yuga or age) when people in general are short-lived, slow in spiritual realization and always disturbed by various anxieties, the best means of spiritual realization is chanting the holy name of the Lord.harer n\xe2\x88\x92ma harer n\xe2\x88\x92ma harer n\xe2\x88\x92maiva kevalamkalau n\xe2\x88\x92sty eva n\xe2\x88\x92sty eva n\xe2\x88\x92sty eva gatir anyath\xe2\x88\x92."In this age of quarrel and hypocrisy the only means of deliverance is chanting the holy name of the Lord. There is no other way. There is no other way. There is no other way."
