TRANSLATION
One should hold one\xc3\x95s body, neck and head erect in a straight line and stare steadily at the tip of the nose. Thus with an unagitated, subdued mind, devoid of fear, completely free from sex life, one should meditate upon Me within the \nheart and make Me the ultimate goal of life.
PURPORTThe goal of life is to know K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, who is situated within the heart of every living being as Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, the four-handed Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au form. The yoga process is practiced in order to discover and see this localized form of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, and not for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa dwelling within one\xc3\x95s heart. One who has no program to realize this Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au-murti is uselessly engaged in mock-yoga practice and is certainly wasting his time. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92 is the ultimate goal of life, and the Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au-murti situated in one\xc3\x95s heart is the object of yoga practice. To realize this Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au-murti within the heart, one has to observe complete abstinence from sex life; therefore one has to leave home and live alone in a secluded place, remaining seated as \nmentioned above. One cannot enjoy sex life daily at home or elsewhere and attend a so-called yoga class and thus become a yog\xe2\x80\x9d. One has to practice controlling the mind and avoiding all kinds of sense gratification, of which sex life is the chief. In the rules of celibacy written by the great sage Y\xe2\x88\x92j\xc5\x81avalkya it is said:karma\xe2\x80\x9a\xe2\x88\x92 manas\xe2\x88\x92 v\xe2\x88\x92c\xe2\x88\x92 sarv\xe2\x88\x92vasth\xe2\x88\x92su sarvad\xe2\x88\x92sarvatra maithu\xe2\x80\x9aa-ty\xe2\x88\x92go brahmacarya\xe2\x80\xb9 pracak\xc5\x92ate."The vow of brahmacarya is meant to help one completely abstain from sex indulgence in work, words and mind\xc3\x91at all times, under all circumstances, and in all places." No one can perform correct yoga practice through sex indulgence. Brahmacarya is taught, therefore, from childhood when one has no knowledge of sex life. Children at the age of five are sent to the guru-kula, or the place of the spiritual master, and the master trains the young boys in the strict discipline of becoming brahmac\