b'realization at which the devotee becomes one with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in the sense that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa becomes everything for the devotee, and the devotee becomes full in loving K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. An intimate relationship between the Lord and the devotee then exists. In that stage, the living entity attains his immortality. Nor is the Personality of Godhead ever out of the sight of the devotee. To merge in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is spiritual annihilation. A devotee takes no such risk. It is stated in the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92:prem\xe2\x88\x92\xc5\x81jana-cchurita-bhakti-vilocanenasanta\xc5\xa1 sadaiva h\xe2\x80\x9edaye\xc5\x92u vilokayantigovindam \xe2\x88\x92di-puru\xc5\x92a\xe2\x80\xb9 tam aha\xe2\x80\xb9 bhaj\xe2\x88\x92mi\xc3\x92I worship the primeval Lord, Govinda, who is always seen by the devotee whose eyes are anointed with the pulp of love. He is seen in His eternal form of \xe2\x80\xa1y\xe2\x88\x92masundara situated within the heart of the devotee." (Bs. 5.38)At this stage, Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa never disappears from the sight of the devotee, nor does the devotee ever lose sight of the Lord. In the case of a yog\xe2\x80\x9d who sees the Lord as Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92 within the heart, the same applies. Such a yog\xe2\x80\x9d turns into a pure devotee and cannot bear to live for a moment with out seeing the \nLord within himself.
