PURPORTThe word bhajete is significant here. Bhajete has its root in the verb bhaj, which is used when there is need of service. The English word "worship" cannot be used in the same sense as bhaja. Worship means to adore, or to show respect and honor to the worthy one. But service with love and faith is \nespecially meant for the Supreme Personality of Godhead. One can avoid worshiping a respectable man or a demigod and may be called discourteous, but one cannot avoid serving the Supreme Lord without being thoroughly condemned. Every living entity is part and parcel of the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and thus every living entity is intended to serve the Supreme Lord by his own constitution. Failing to do this, he falls down. The Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam confirms this as follows:ya e\xc5\x92\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\xb9 puru\xc5\x92a\xe2\x80\xb9 s\xe2\x88\x92k\xc5\x92\xe2\x88\x92d \xe2\x88\x92tma-prabhavam \xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9cvaramna bhajanty avaj\xe2\x88\x92nanti sth\xe2\x88\x92n\xe2\x88\x92d bhra\xc5\x92\xc4\xb1\xe2\x88\x92 patanty adha\xc5\xa1."Anyone who does not render service and neglects his duty unto the Primeval Lord, who is the source of all living entities, will certainly fall down from his constitutional position."'
b'In this verse also the word bhajanti is used. Therefore, bhajanti is applicable to the Supreme Lord only, whereas the word "worship" can be applied to demigods or to any other common living entity. The word avaj\xe2\x88\x92nanti, used in this verse of \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam, is also found in the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92: avaj\xe2\x88\x92nanti \n"Only the fools and rascals deride the Supreme Personality of Godhead Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa." Such fools take it upon themselves to write commentaries on the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 without an attitude of service to the Lord. Consequently they cannot properly distinguish between the word bhajanti and the word "worship."The culmination of all kinds of yoga practices lies in bhakti-yoga. All other yogas are but means to come to the point of bhakti in bhakti-yoga. Yoga actually means bhakti-yoga; all other yogas are progressions toward the destination of bhakti-yoga. From the beginning of karma-yoga to the end of bhakti-yoga is a long way to self-realization. Karma-yoga, without fruitive results, is the beginning of this path. When karma-yoga increases in knowledge and \nrenunciation, the stage is called j\xc5\x81\xe2\x88\x92na-yoga. When j\xc5\x81\xe2\x88\x92na-yoga increases in meditation on the Supersoul by different physical processes, and the mind is on Him, it is called a\xc5\x92\xc4\xb1\xe2\x88\x92\xef\xac\x81ga-yoga. And, when one surpasses the a\xc5\x92\xc4\xb1\xe2\x88\x92\xef\xac\x81ga-yoga and comes to the point of the Supreme Personality of Godhead K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, it is called bhakti-yoga, the culmination. Factually, bhakti-yoga is the ultimate goal, but to analyze bhakti-yoga minutely one has to understand these other yogas. The yog\xe2\x80\x9d who is progressive is therefore on the true path of eternal good \nfortune. One who sticks to a particular point and does not make further progress is called by that particular name: karma-yog\xe2\x80\x9d, j\xc5\x81\xe2\x88\x92na-yog\xe2\x80\x9d or dhy\xe2\x88\x92na-yog\xe2\x80\x9d, r\xe2\x88\x92ja-yog\xe2\x80\x9d, ha\xc4\xb1ha-yog\xe2\x80\x9d, etc. If one is fortunate enough to come to the point of bhakti-yoga, it is to be understood that he has surpassed all the other yogas. Therefore, to become K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious is the highest stage of yoga, just as, when we speak of Himalayan, we refer to the world\xc3\x95s highest mountains, of which the highest peak, Mount Everest, is considered to be the culmination.\nIt is by great fortune that one comes to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness on the path of bhakti-yoga to become well situated according to the Vedic direction. The ideal yog\xe2\x80\x9d concentrates his attention on K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, who is called \xe2\x80\xa1y\xe2\x88\x92masundara, who is as beautifully colored as a cloud, whose lotus-like face is as effulgent as the sun, whose dress is brilliant with jewels and whose body is flower garlanded. Illuminating all sides is His gorgeous luster, which is called the brahmajyoti. He incarnates in different forms such as R\xe2\x88\x92ma, N\xe2\x80\x9esi\xe2\x80\xb9ha, Var\xe2\x88\x92ha '
b'and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and He descends like a human being, as the son of Mother Ya\xe2\x80\x9cod\xe2\x88\x92, and He is known as K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, Govinda and V\xe2\x88\x92sudeva. He is the perfect child, husband, friend and master, and He is full with all opulences and transcendental qualities. If one remains fully conscious of these features of the Lord, he is called the highest yog\xe2\x80\x9d.This stage of highest perfection in yoga can be attained only by bhakti-yoga, as \nis confirmed in all Vedic literature:yasya deve par\xe2\x88\x92 bhaktir yath\xe2\x88\x92 deve tath\xe2\x88\x92 gurau.tasyaite kathit\xe2\x88\x92 hy arth\xe2\x88\x92\xc5\xa1 prak\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9cante mah\xe2\x88\x92tmana\xc5\xa1."Only unto those great souls who have implicit faith in both the Lord and the spiritual master are all the imports of Vedic knowledge automatically revealed."Bhaktir asya bhajana\xe2\x80\xb9 tadih\xe2\x88\x92mutrop\xe2\x88\x92dhi nair\xe2\x88\x92syen\xe2\x88\x92mu\xc5\x92min mana\xc5\xa1 kalpanam; etad eva nai\xc5\x92karmyam. \xc3\x92Bhakti means devotional service to the Lord \nwhich is free from desire for material profit, either in this life or in the next. Devoid of such inclinations, one should fully absorb the mind in the Supreme. That is the purpose of nai\xc5\x92karmya.\xc3\x93These are some of the means for performance of bhakti or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, the highest perfectional stage of the yoga system.Thus end the Bhaktivedanta Purports to the Sixth Chapter of the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 in the matter of S\xe2\x88\x92\xef\xac\x81khya-yoga Brahma-vidy\xe2\x88\x92.'
