ial nature, and their manifestations with paraphernalia.One should therefore begin yoga practice as directed in the last verse of the Sixth Chapter. Concentration of the mind upon K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa the Supreme is made possible by prescribed devotional service in nine different forms, of which \xe2\x80\x9crava\xe2\x80\x9aam is the first and most important. The Lord therefore says to Arjuna, "tat \xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x80\x9e\xe2\x80\x9au," or "Hear from Me." No one can be a greater authority than K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and therefore by hearing from Him one receives the greatest opportunity for \nprogress in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness. One has therefore to learn from K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa '
