PURPORTThe Supreme Personality of Godhead has innumerable energies, and all these energies are divine. Although the living entities are part of His energies and are therefore divine, due to contact with material energy, their original superior power is covered. Being thus covered by material energy, one cannot possibly overcome its influence. As previously stated, both the material and spiritual natures, being emanations from the Supreme Personality of Godhead, are eternal. The living entities belong to the eternal superior nature of the Lord, but due to contamination by the inferior nature, matter, their illusion is \nalso eternal. The conditioned soul is therefore called nitya-baddha, or eternally conditioned. No one can trace out the history of his becoming conditioned at a certain date in material history. Consequently, his release from the clutches of material nature is very difficult, even though that material nature is an inferior energy, because material energy is ultimately conducted by the supreme will, which the living entity cannot overcome. Inferior material nature is defined herein as divine nature due to its divine connection and \nmovement by the divine will. Being conducted by divine will, material nature, although inferior, acts so wonderfully in the construction and destruction of the cosmic manifestation. The Vedas confirm this as follows:m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\xb9 tu prak\xe2\x80\x9eti\xe2\x80\xb9 vidy\xe2\x88\x92n m\xe2\x88\x92yina\xe2\x80\xb9 tu mahe\xe2\x80\x9cvaram."Although m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92 [illusion] is false or temporary, the background of m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92 is the supreme magician, the Personality of Godhead, who is Mahe\xe2\x80\x9cvara, the \nsupreme controller."Another meaning of gu\xe2\x80\x9aa is rope; it is to be understood that the conditioned soul is tightly tied by the ropes of illusion. A man bound by the '
b'hands and feet cannot free himself\xc3\x91he must be helped by a person who is unbound. Because the bound cannot help the bound, the rescuer must be liberated. Therefore, only Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, or His bona fide representative the spiritual master, can release the conditioned soul. Without such superior help, one cannot be freed from the bondage of material nature. Devotional service, or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, can help one gain such release. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, being the Lord of illusory energy, can order this insurmountable energy to release the conditioned soul. He orders this release out of His causeless mercy on the \nsurrendered soul and out of His paternal affection for the living entity who is originally a beloved son of the Lord. Therefore surrender unto the lotus feet of the Lord is the only means to get free from the clutches of the stringent material nature.The words m\xe2\x88\x92m eva are also significant. M\xe2\x88\x92m means unto K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa (Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au) only, and not Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 or \xe2\x80\xa1iva. Although Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1iva are greatly elevated and are almost on the level of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, it is not possible for such incarnations of r\xe2\x88\x92jo-gu\xe2\x80\x9aa (passion) and tamo-gu\xe2\x80\x9aa (ignorance) to release the conditioned soul from the clutches of m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92. In other words, both Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1iva are also under the influence of m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92. Only Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au is the master of m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92; therefore He can alone give release to the conditioned soul. The Vedas confirm this in the phrase tvam eva viditv\xe2\x88\x92 or "Freedom is possible only by understanding K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa." Even Lord \xe2\x80\xa1iva affirms that liberation can be achieved only by the mercy of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au. Lord \xe2\x80\xa1iva