PURPORTThose who are worshipers of demigods have been described as less intelligent persons, and here the impersonalists are similarly described. Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in His personal form is here speaking before Arjuna, and still, due to ignorance, impersonalists argue that the Supreme Lord ultimately has no form. Y\xe2\x88\x92mun\xe2\x88\x92c\xe2\x88\x92rya, a great devotee of the Lord in the disciplic succession from R\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x88\x92nuj\xe2\x88\x92c\xe2\x88\x92rya, has written two very appropriate verses in this connection. He says, "My dear Lord, devotees like Vy\xe2\x88\x92sadeva and N\xe2\x88\x92rada know You to be \nthe Personality of Godhead. By understanding different Vedic literatures, one can come to know Your characteristics, Your form and Your activities, and one can thus understand that You are the Supreme Personality of Godhead. But those who are in the modes of passion and ignorance, the demons, the nondevotees, cannot understand You. They are unable to understand You. However expert such nondevotees may be in discussing Ved\xe2\x88\x92nta and the Upani\xc5\x92ads and other Vedic literatures, it is not possible for them to \nunderstand the Personality of Godhead."In the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 it is stated that the Personality of Godhead cannot be understood simply by study of the Ved\xe2\x88\x92nta literature. Only by the mercy of the Supreme Lord can the Personality of the Supreme be known. Therefore in this verse it is clearly stated that not only the worshipers of the demigods are less intelligent, but those nondevotees who are engaged in Ved\xe2\x88\x92nta and speculation on Vedic literature without any tinge of true K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness \nare also less intelligent, and for them it is not possible to understand God\xc3\x95s personal nature. Persons who are under the impression that the Absolute Truth is impersonal are described as asuras, which means one who does not know the ultimate feature of the Absolute Truth. In the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam it is stated that supreme realization begins from the impersonal Brahman and then rises to the localized Supersoul!but the ultimate word in the Absolute Truth is the Personality of Godhead. Modern impersonalists are still less \nintelligent, for they do not even follow their great predecessor, \xe2\x80\xa1a\xef\xac\x81kar\xe2\x88\x92c\xe2\x88\x92rya, who has specifically stated that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead. Impersonalists, therefore, not knowing the Supreme Truth, think K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to be only the son of Devak\xe2\x80\x9d and Vasudeva, or a prince, or a powerful living entity. This is also condemned in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92: "Only the fools regard Me as an ordinary person." The fact is that no one can understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa without '
b'rendering devotional service and without developing K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness. The G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 confirms this.One cannot understand the Supreme Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, or His form, quality or name simply by mental speculation or by discussing Vedic literature. One must understand Him by devotional service. When one is fully engaged in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, beginning by chanting the mah\xe2\x88\x92mantra!Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, Hare Hare/Hare R\xe2\x88\x92ma, Hare R\xe2\x88\x92ma, R\xe2\x88\x92ma R\xe2\x88\x92ma, Hare Hare!then only can one understand the \nSupreme Personality of Godhead. Nondevotee impersonalists think that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has a body made of this material nature and that all His activities, His form and everything, are m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92. These impersonalists are known as M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d. They do not know the ultimate truth.The twentieth verse clearly states: "Those who are blinded by lusty desires surrender unto the different demigods." It is accepted that besides the Supreme Personality of Godhead, there are demigods who have their different planets (Bg. 7.23), and the Lord also has a planet. It is also stated that the worshipers of the demigods go to the different planets of the demigods, and those who are devotees of Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa go to the K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aaloka planet. Although this is clearly stated, the foolish impersonalists still maintain that the Lord is formless and that these forms are impositions. From the study of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 does it appear that \nthe demigods and their abodes are impersonal? Clearly, neither the demigods nor K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the Supreme Personality of Godhead, are impersonal. They are all persons; Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and He has His own planet, and the demigods have theirs.Therefore the monistic contention that ultimate truth is formless and that form is imposed does not hold true. It is clearly stated here that it is not imposed. From the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 we can clearly understand that the forms of the \ndemigods and the form of the Supreme Lord are simultaneously existing and that Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is sac-cid-\xe2\x88\x92nanda, eternal blissful knowledge. The Vedas also confirm that the Supreme Absolute Truth is \xe2\x88\x92nandamaya, or full of blissful pleasure, and that He is abhy\xe2\x88\x92s\xe2\x88\x92t, by nature the reservoir of unlimited auspicious qualities. And in the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 the Lord says that although He is aja (unborn), He still appears. These are the facts that we should understand from the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. We cannot understand how the Supreme Personality of Godhead \ncan be impersonal; the imposition theory of the impersonalist monist is false as '
b'far as the statements of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 are concerned. It is clear herein that the Supreme Absolute Truth, Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, has both form and personality.
