PURPORTIn this verse Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa stresses the importance of remembering Him. One\xc3\x95s memory of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is revived by chanting the mah\xe2\x88\x92mantra, Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. By this practice of chanting and hearing the sound vibration of the Supreme Lord, one\xc3\x95s ear, tongue and mind are engaged. This mystic meditation is very easy to practice, and it helps one attain the Supreme Lord. Puru\xc5\x92am means enjoyer. Although living entities belong to the marginal energy of the Supreme Lord, they are in material contamination. They think themselves enjoyers, but they are not the supreme enjoyer. Here it is clearly stated that the supreme enjoyer is the Supreme Personality of Godhead in His different manifestations and plenary expansions as N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa, V\xe2\x88\x92sudeva, etc.The devotees can constantly think of the object of worship, the Supreme Lord, in any of His features, N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, R\xe2\x88\x92ma, etc., by chanting Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. This practice will purify him, and at the end of his life, due to his constant \nchanting, he will be transferred to the kingdom of God. Yoga practice is meditation on the Supersoul within; similarly, by chanting Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa one \nfixes his mind always on the Supreme Lord. The mind is fickle, and therefore it is necessary to engage the mind by force to think of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. One example often given is that of the caterpillar that thinks of becoming a butterfly and so is transformed into a butterfly in the same life. Similarly, if we constantly think of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, it is certain that at the end of our lives we shall have the same \nbodily constitution as K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.
