PURPORTThe duration of the material universe is limited. It is manifested in cycles of kalpas. A kalpa is a day of Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, and one day of Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 consists of a thousand cycles of four yugas or ages: Satya, Tret\xe2\x88\x92, Dv\xe2\x88\x92para, and Kali. The cycle of Satya is characterized by virtue, wisdom and religion, there being practically no ignorance and vice, and the yuga lasts 1,728,000 years. In the Tret\xe2\x88\x92-yuga vice is introduced, and this yuga lasts 1,296,000 years. In the Dv\xe2\x88\x92para-yuga there is an even greater decline in virtue and religion, vice \nincreasing, and this yuga lasts 864,000 years. And finally in Kali-yuga (the yuga we have now been experiencing over the past 5,000 years) there is an abundance of strife, ignorance, irreligion and vice, true virtue being practically nonexistent, and this yuga lasts 432,000 years. In Kali-yuga vice increases to such a point that at the termination of the yuga the Supreme Lord Himself appears as the Kalki avatara, vanquishes the demons, saves His \ndevotees, and commences another Satya-yuga. Then the process is set rolling \nagain. These four yugas, rotating a thousand times, comprise one day of Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, the creator god, and the same number comprise one night. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 lives one hundred of such \xc3\x92years\xc3\x93 and then dies. These \xc3\x92hundred years\xc3\x93 by earth calculations total to 311 trillion and 40 million earth years. By these calculations the life of Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 seems fantastic and interminable, but from the viewpoint of eternity it is as brief as a lightning flash. In the causal ocean there are innumerable Brahm\xe2\x88\x92s rising and disappearing like bubbles in the \nAtlantic. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and his creation are all part of the material universe, and therefore they are in constant flux.In the material universe not even Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 is free from the process of birth, old age, disease and death. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, however, is directly engaged in the service of the Supreme Lord in the management of this universe!therefore he at once attains liberation. Elevated sanny\xe2\x88\x92s\xe2\x80\x9ds are promoted to Brahm\xe2\x88\x92\xc3\x95s particular planet, Brahmaloka, which is the highest planet in the material universe and \nwhich survives all the heavenly planets in the upper strata of the planetary system, but in due course Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and all inhabitants of Brahmaloka are subject to death, according to the law of material nature.'
