onal service, one cannot understand what is the Personality of Godhead. In the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam it is also confirmed that when one becomes purified by executing the process of devotional service, especially by hearing \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam or Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 from realized souls, then he can understand the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa or the science of God. Eva\xe2\x80\xb9 prasanna-manaso \nbhagavad-bhakti-yogata\xc5\xa1. When one\xc3\x95s heart is cleared of all nonsense, then one can understand what God is. Thus the process of devotional service, of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, is the king of all education and the king of all confidential knowledge. It is the purest form of religion, and it can be executed joyfully without difficulty. Therefore one should adopt it.'
