TRANSLATION
Fools deride Me when I descend in the human form. They do not know My transcendental nature and My supreme dominion over all that be.
PURPORTFrom the other explanations of the previous verses in this chapter, it is clear that the Supreme Personality of Godhead, although appearing like a human being, is not a common man. The Personality of Godhead, who conducts the creation, maintenance and annihilation of the complete cosmic manifestation, cannot be a human being. Yet there are many foolish men who \nconsider K\xe2\x80\x9e,s\xe2\x80\x9aa to be merely a powerful man and nothing more. Actually, He is the original Supreme Personality, as is confirmed in the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 (i\xe2\x80\x9cvara\xc5\xa1 parama\xc5\xa1 k\xe2\x80\x9es\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc5\xa1); He is the Supreme Lord.\nThere are many \xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9cvaras, controllers, and one appears greater than another. In the ordinary management of affairs in the material world, we find some official or director, and above him there is a secretary, and above him a minister, and above him a president. Each of them is a controller, but one is '
b'controlled by another. In the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 it is said that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the supreme controller; there are many controllers undoubtedly both in the material and spiritual world, but K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the supreme controller (\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9cvara\xc5\xa1 parama\xc5\xa1 k\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc5\xa1), and His body is sac-cid-\xe2\x88\x92nanda, non-material.\nMaterial bodies cannot perform the wonderful acts described in previous verses. His body is eternal, blissful and full of knowledge. Although He is not a common man, the foolish deride Him and consider Him to be a man. His body is called here m\xe2\x88\x92nu\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9dm because He is acting just like a man, a friend of \nArjuna\xc3\x95s, a politician involved in the Battle of Kuruk\xc5\x92etra. In so many ways He is acting just like an ordinary man, but actually His body is sac-cid-\xe2\x88\x92nanda-vigraha!eternal bliss and knowledge absolute. This is confirmed in the Vedic \nlanguage also  \xc3\x92I offer my obeisances unto the Supreme Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, who is the eternal blissful form of knowledge.\xc3\x93 There are other descriptions in the Vedic language also. Tam eka\xe2\x80\xb9 govindam: \xc3\x92You are Govinda, the pleasure of the senses and the cows.\xc3\x93 Sac-cid-\xe2\x88\x92nanda-vigraham: \xc3\x92And Your form is transcendental, full of knowledge, bliss and eternality.\xc3\x93Despite the transcendental qualities of Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s body, its full bliss and knowledge, there are many so-called scholars and commentators of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 who deride K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as an ordinary man. The scholar may be born an \nextraordinary man due to his previous good work, but this conception of \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is due to a poor fund of knowledge. Therefore he is called for only foolish persons consider K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to be an ordinary human being because they do not know the confidential activities of the Supreme Lord and His different energies. They do not know that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s body is a symbol of complete knowledge and bliss, that He is the proprietor of everything that be and that He can award liberation to anyone. Because they do not know that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has so many transcendental qualifications, they deride Him.Nor do they know that the appearance of the Supreme Personality of Godhead \nin this material world is a manifestation of His internal energy. He is the master of the material energy. As has been explained in several places (mama m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92 duratyay\xe2\x88\x92), He claims that the material energy, although very powerful, \nis under His control, and whoever surrenders unto Him can get out of the control of this material energy. If a soul surrendered to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa can get out of the influence of material energy, then how can the Supreme Lord, who conducts the creation, maintenance and annihilation of the whole cosmic '
b'nature, have a material body like us? So this conception of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is complete foolishness. Foolish persons, however, cannot conceive that the Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, appearing just like an ordinary man, can be the controller of all the atoms and of the gigantic manifestation of the universal form. The biggest and the minutest are beyond their conception, so they cannot imagine that a form like that of a human being can simultaneously control the infinite and the minute. Actually although He is controlling the infinite and the finite, He is apart from all this manifestation. It is clearly stated concerning \nHis yogam ai\xe2\x80\x9cvaram, His inconceivable transcendental energy, that He can control the infinite and the finite simultaneously and that He can remain aloof from them. Although the foolish cannot imagine how K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, who appears just like a human being, can control the infinite and the finite, those who are pure devotees accept this, for they know that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead. Therefore they completely surrender unto Him and engage in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, devotional service of the Lord.\nThere are many controversies amongst the impersonalists and the personalists about the Lord\xc3\x95s appearance as a human being. But if we consult Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam, the authoritative texts for understanding the science \nof K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, then we can understand that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead. He is not an ordinary man, although He appeared on this earth as an ordinary human. In the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam, First Canto, First Chapter, when the sages inquire about the activities of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, it is stated that His \nappearance as a man bewilders the foolish. No human being could perform the wonderful acts that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa performed while He was present on this earth. When K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa appeared before His father and mother, Vasudeva and Devak\xe2\x80\x9d, He appeared with four hands, but after the prayers of the parents, He transformed Himself into an ordinary child. His appearance as an ordinary human being is one of the features of His transcendental body. In the Eleventh Chapter of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 also it is stated, etc. Arjuna \nprayed to see again that form of four hands, and when K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa was thus petitioned by Arjuna, He again assumed His original form. All these different features of the Supreme Lord are certainly not those of an ordinary human being.Some of those who deride K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, who are infected with the M\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92v\xe2\x88\x92d\xe2\x80\x9d philosophy, quote the following verse from the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam to prove that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is just an ordinary man: '
b'sad\xe2\x88\x92: \xc3\x92The Supreme is present in every living entity.\xc3\x93 (Bh\xe2\x88\x92g. 3.29.21) We should better take note of this particular verse from the Vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava \xe2\x88\x92c\xe2\x88\x92ryas like J\xe2\x80\x9dva Gosv\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9d instead of following the interpretation of unauthorized persons \nwho deride K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. J\xe2\x80\x9dva Gosv\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9d, commenting on this verse, says that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, in His plenary expansion as Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, is situated in the moving and the nonmoving entities as the Supersoul, so any neophyte devotee who simply gives his attention to the the form of the Supreme Lord in the temple, and does not respect other living entities is uselessly worshiping the \nform of the Lord in the temple. There are three kinds of devotees of the Lord, and the neophyte is in the lowest stage. The neophyte devotee gives more attention to the Deity in the temple than to other devotees, so J\xe2\x80\x9dva Gosv\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9d warns that this sort of mentality should be corrected. A devotee should see that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is present in everyone\xc3\x95s heart as Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92; therefore every body is the embodiment or the temple of the Supreme Lord, and as such, as one offers respect to the temple of the Lord, he should similarly properly respect \neach and every body in whom the Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92 dwells. Everyone should therefore be given proper respect and should not be neglected.There are also many impersonalists who deride temple worship. They say that since God is everywhere, why should one restrict himself to temple worship? But if God is everywhere, is He not in the temple or in the Deity? Although the personalist and the impersonalist will fight with one another perpetually, a perfect devotee in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness knows that although K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the \nSupreme Personality, He is all-pervading, as is confirmed in the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92. Although His personal abode is Goloka V\xe2\x80\x9end\xe2\x88\x92vana and He is always \nstaying there, still, by His different manifestations of energy and by His plenary expansion, He is present everywhere in all parts of the material and spiritual creation.
