Those who are thus bewildered are attracted by demonic and atheistic views. In that deluded condition, their hopes for liberation, their fruitive activities, and their culture of knowledge are all defeated.
PURPORTThere are many devotees who assume themselves to be in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness and devotional service but at heart do not accept the Supreme Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, as the Absolute Truth. For them, the fruit of devotional service\xc3\x91going back to Godhead\xc3\x91will never be tasted. Similarly, those who are engaged in fruitive, pious activities and who are ultimately hoping to be liberated from this material entanglement will never be successful either because they deride the Supreme Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. In other words, persons who mock K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa are to be understood to be demonic or \natheistic. As described in the Seventh Chapter of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, such demonic miscreants never surrender to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Therefore their mental speculations to arrive at the Absolute Truth bring them to the false conclusion that the ordinary living entity and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa are one and the same. With such a false conviction, they think that the body of any human being is now simply covered by material nature and that as soon as one is liberated from this material body there is no difference between God and himself. This attempt to \nbecome one with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa will be baffled because of delusion. Such atheistic and demoniac cultivation of spiritual knowledge is always futile. That is the indication of this verse. For such persons, cultivation of the knowledge in the Vedic literature, like the and the Upani\xc5\x92ads, is always baffled.It is a great offense, therefore, to consider K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the Supreme Personality of Godhead, to be an ordinary man. Those who do so are certainly deluded because they cannot understand the eternal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. In the B\xe2\x80\x9ehad-'
b'vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava mantra it is clearly stated that one who considers the body of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to be material should be driven out from all rituals and activities of the \xe2\x80\x9cruti. And if one by chance sees his face, he should at once take bath in the Ganges \nto rid himself of infection. People jeer at K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa because they are envious of the Supreme Personality of Godhead. Their destiny is certainly to take birth after birth in the species of atheistic and demoniac life. Perpetually, their real knowledge will remain under delusion, and gradually they will regress to the darkest region of creation.
