PURPORTHere Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, having established that He is the only enjoyer, the primeval Lord, and the real object of all sacrificial offerings, reveals what types of sacrifices He desires to be offered. If one wishes to engage in devotional service to the Supreme in order to be purified and to reach the goal of life\xc3\x91\nthe transcendental loving service of God\xc3\x91then he should find out what the Lord desires of him. One who loves K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa will give Him whatever He wants, and he avoids offering anything which is undesirable or unasked for. Thus, meat, fish and eggs should not be offered to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. If He desired such things as offerings, He would have said so. Instead He clearly requests that a leaf, fruit, flowers and water be given to Him, and He says of this offering, \xc3\x92I will accept it.\xc3\x93 Therefore, we should understand that He will not accept meat, fish and \neggs. Vegetables, grains, fruits, milk and water are the proper foods for human beings and are prescribed by Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa Himself. Whatever else we eat cannot be offered to Him, since He will not accept it. Thus we cannot be acting on the level of loving devotion if we offer such foods.In the Third Chapter, verse thirteen, \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa explains that only the remains of sacrifice are purified and fit for consumption by those who are seeking advancement in life and release from the clutches of the material \nentanglement. Those who do not make an offering of their food, He says in the same verse, are said to be eating only sin. In other words, their every mouthful is simply deepening their involvement in the complexities of material nature. But preparing nice, simple vegetable dishes, offering them before the picture or Deity of Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and bowing down and praying for Him to accept such a humble offering, enable one to advance steadily in life, to purify the body, and to create fine brain tissues which will lead to clear \nthinking. Above all, the offering should be made with an attitude of love. '
b'K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has no need of food, since He already possesses everything that be, yet He will accept the offering of one who desires to please Him in that way. The important element, in preparation, in serving and in offering, is to act with love for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.The impersonalist philosophers, who wish to maintain that the Absolute Truth is without senses, cannot comprehend this verse of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. To them, it is either a metaphor or proof of the mundane character of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the \nspeaker of the G\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. But, in actuality, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the Supreme Godhead, has senses, \nand it is stated that His senses are interchangeable; in other words, one sense can perform the function of any other. This is what it means to say that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is absolute. Lacking senses, He could hardly be considered full in all opulences. In the Seventh Chapter, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has explained that He impregnates the living entities into material nature. This is done by His looking upon material nature. And so in this instance, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s hearing the devotee\xc3\x95s words of love in offering foodstuffs is wholly identical with His eating and actually tasting. This \npoint should be emphasized: because of His absolute position, His hearing is wholly identical with His eating and tasting. Only the devotee, who accepts K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as He describes Himself, without interpretation, can understand that the Supreme Absolute Truth can eat food and enjoy it.
