Engage your mind always in thinking of Me, offer obeisances and worship Me. Being completely absorbed in Me, surely you will come to Me.
PURPORTIn this verse it is clearly indicated that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness is the only means of being delivered from the clutches of this contaminated material world. Sometimes unscrupulous commentators distort the meaning of what is clearly stated here: that all devotional service should be offered to the Supreme Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Unfortunately, unscrupulous commentators divert the mind of the reader to that which is not at all feasible. Such commentators do not know that there is no difference between K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s mind and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is not an ordinary human being; He is Absolute Truth. His body, mind and He Himself are one and absolute. It is stated in the Pur\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, as it is quoted by Bhaktisiddh\xe2\x88\x92nta Sarasvat\xe2\x80\x9d Gosv\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9d in his Anubh\xe2\x88\x92\xc5\x92ya comments on Caitanya-carit\xe2\x88\x92mrta, Fifth Chapter, \xe2\x80\xa2di-l\xe2\x80\x9dl\xe2\x88\x92, verses 41\xc3\x9048, \n\xc3\x92deha-dehi-vibhedo \xc3\x95ya\xe2\x80\xb9 ne\xe2\x80\x9cvare vidyate kvacit,\xc3\x93 which means that there is no difference in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the Supreme Lord, between Himself and His body. But, because they do not know this science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the commentators hide K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and divide His personality from His mind or from His body. Although this is sheer ignorance of the science of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, some men make profit out of \nmisleading the people.There are some who are demonic; they also think of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, but enviously, just like King Ka\xe2\x80\xb9sa, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s uncle. He was also thinking of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa always, but he thought of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as his enemy. He was always in anxiety, wondering when K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa would come to kill him. That kind of thinking will not help us. One should be thinking of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in devotional love. That is bhakti. One should cultivate the knowledge of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa continually. What is that favorable \ncultivation? It is to learn from a bona fide teacher. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme '
b'Personality of Godhead, and we have several times explained that His body is not material, but is eternal, blissful knowledge. This kind of talk about K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa will help one become a devotee. Otherwise, understanding K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa from the wrong source will prove fruitless.One should therefore engage his mind in the eternal form, the primal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; with conviction in his heart that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme, he should engage himself in worship. There are hundreds of thousands of temples in India for the worship of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and devotional service is practiced there. \nWhen such practice is made, one has to offer obeisances to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. One should lower his head before the Deity and engage his mind, his body, his activities!everything. That will make one fully absorbed in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa without deviation. This will help one transfer into the K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aaloka. One should not be deviated by unscrupulous commentators. One must engage in the nine different processes of devotional service, beginning with hearing and chanting about K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Pure devotional service is the highest achievement of human \nsociety.In the Seventh and Eighth Chapters of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, pure devotional service to the Lord has been explained, apart from the yoga of knowledge and mystic yoga or fruitive activities. Those who are not purely sanctified may be attracted by different features of the Lord, like the impersonal brahmajyoti and localized Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, but a pure devotee directly takes to the service of the \nSupreme Lord.\nThere is a beautiful poem about K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in which it is clearly stated that any person who is engaged in the worship of demigods is most unintelligent and cannot achieve at any time the supreme award of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. The devotee, in the beginning, may sometimes fall from the standard, but still he should be considered superior to all other philosophers and yog\xe2\x80\x9ds. One who always engages in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness should be understood to be the perfect saintly person. His accidental nondevotional activities will diminish, and he will soon \nbe situated without any doubt in complete perfection. The pure devotee has no actual chance to fall down because the Supreme Godhead personally takes care of His pure devotees. Therefore, the intelligent person should take directly to this process of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness and happily live in this material world. He will eventually receive the supreme award of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.'
b'Thus end the Bhaktivedanta Purports to the Ninth Chapter of the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 in the matter of the Most Confidential Knowledge.'
