PURPORTAs stated in the Brahma-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92, Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Lord. No one is greater than Him; He is the cause of all causes. Here it is also stated by the Lord personally that He is the cause of all the demigods and sages. Even the demigods and great sages cannot understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; they can understand neither His name nor His personality, so what is the position of the so-called scholars of this tiny planet? No one can understand why this Supreme God comes to earth as an ordinary human being and executes such commonplace and yet wonderful activities. One should know, then, that scholarship is not the qualification necessary to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Even the demigods and the \ngreat sages have tried to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa by their mental speculation, and they have failed to do so. In the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam also it is clearly said that even the great demigods are not able to understand the Supreme Personality of Godhead. They can speculate to the limits of their imperfect senses and can reach the opposite conclusion of impersonalism, of something not manifested by the three qualities of material nature, or they can imagine something by mental speculation, but it is not possible to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa by such foolish \nspeculation.Here the Lord indirectly says that if anyone wants to know the Absolute Truth, \xc3\x92Here I am present as the Supreme Personality of Godhead. I am the Supreme.\xc3\x93 One should know this. Although one cannot understand the inconceivable Lord who is personally present, He nonetheless exists. We can actually understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, who is eternal, full of bliss and knowledge, simply by studying His words in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam. The \nimpersonal Brahman can be conceived by persons who are already in the '
b'inferior energy of the Lord, but the Personality of Godhead cannot be conceived unless one is in the transcendental position.Because most men cannot understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in His actual situation, out of His causeless mercy He descends to show favor to such speculators. Yet despite the Supreme Lord\xc3\x95s uncommon activities, these speculators, due to contamination in the material energy, still think that the impersonal Brahman is the Supreme. Only the devotees who are fully surrendered unto the Supreme Lord can understand, by the grace of the Supreme Personality, that He is K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. \nThe devotees of the Lord do not bother about the impersonal Brahman conception of God; their faith and devotion bring them to surrender immediately unto the Supreme Lord, and out of the causeless mercy of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, they can understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. No one else can understand Him. So even great sages agree: What is \xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, what is the Supreme? It is He whom we have to worship.
