The seven great sages and before them the four other great sages and the Manus [progenitors of mankind] are born out of My mind, and all creatures in these \nplanets descend from them.'
b'
PURPORTThe Lord is giving a genealogical synopsis of the universal population. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 is the original creature born out of the energy of the Supreme Lord known as Hira\xe2\x80\x9ayagarbha. And from Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 all the seven great sages, and before them four other great sages, named Sanaka, Sananda, San\xe2\x88\x92tana, and Sanatkum\xe2\x88\x92ra, and the Manus, are manifest. All these twenty-five great sages are known as the patriarchs of the living entities all over the universe. There are innumerable universes and innumerable planets within each universe, and \neach planet is full of population of different varieties. All of them are born of these twenty-five patriarchs. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 underwent penance for one thousand years of the demigods before he realized by the grace of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa how to create. Then from Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, Sanaka, Sananda, San\xe2\x88\x92tana, and Sanatkum\xe2\x88\x92ra came out, then Rudra, and then the seven sages, and in this way all the br\xe2\x88\x92hma\xe2\x80\x9aas and k\xc5\x92atriyas are born out of the energy of the Supreme Personality of Godhead. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 is known as pit\xe2\x88\x92maha, the grandfather, and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is known as the prapit\xe2\x88\x92-maha, the father of the grandfather. That is stated in the Eleventh Chapter of the Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. (Bg. 11.39)
