PURPORTIt has already been explained by the Lord that amongst all the Vedas, the S\xe2\x88\x92ma-veda is rich with beautiful songs played by the various demigods.One of these songs is the B\xe2\x80\x9ehat-s\xe2\x88\x92ma, which has an exquisite melody and is sung at midnight.In Sanskrit, there are definite rules that regulate poetry; rhyme and meter are not written whimsically, as in much modern poetry. Amongst the regulated \npoetry, the G\xe2\x88\x92yatr\xe2\x80\x9d mantra, which is chanted by the duly qualified br\xe2\x88\x92hma\xe2\x80\x9aas, is the most prominent. The G\xe2\x88\x92yatr\xe2\x80\x9d mantra is mentioned in the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam. Because the G\xe2\x88\x92yatr\xe2\x80\x9d mantra is especially meant for God realization, it represents the Supreme Lord. This mantra is meant for spiritually advanced people, and when one attains success in chanting it, he can enter into the transcendental position of the Lord. One must first acquire the qualities of the perfectly situated person, the qualities of goodness \naccording to the laws of material nature, in order to chant the G\xe2\x88\x92yatr\xe2\x80\x9d mantra. The G\xe2\x88\x92yatr\xe2\x80\x9d mantra is very important in Vedic civilization and is considered \nto be the sound incarnation of Brahman. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 is its initiator, and it is passed down from him in disciplic succession.The months of November and December are considered the best of all months because in India grains are collected from the fields at this time, and the people become very happy. Of course spring is a season universally liked \nbecause it is neither too hot nor too cold, and the flowers and trees blossom and flourish. In spring there are also many ceremonies commemorating K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s pastimes; therefore this is considered to be the most joyful of all seasons, and it is the representative of the Supreme Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.
