PURPORTThe Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is worshipable as a father is worshipable for his son. He is the spiritual master because He originally gave the Vedic instructions to Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, and presently He is also instructing Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 to Arjuna; therefore He is the original spiritual master, and any bona fide spiritual master at the present moment must be a descendant in the line of disciplic succession stemming from K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Without being a representative of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, one cannot become a teacher or spiritual master of transcendental subject matter.\nThe Lord is being paid obeisances in all respects. He is of immeasurable greatness. No one can be greater than the Supreme Personality of Godhead, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, because no one is equal to or higher than K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa within any manifestation, spiritual or material. Everyone is below Him. No one can excel Him.The Supreme Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has senses and a body like the ordinary man, but for Him there is no difference between His senses, body, mind and Himself. \nFoolish persons who do not know Him perfectly say that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is different from His soul, mind, heart and everything else. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is absolute; therefore His activities and potencies are supreme. It is also stated that He does not have senses like ours. He can perform all sensual activities; therefore His senses are neither imperfect nor limited. No one can be greater than Him, no one can be equal to Him, and everyone is lower than Him.Whoever knows His transcendental body, activities and perfection, after \nquitting his body, returns to Him and doesn\xc3\x95t come back again to this miserable world. Therefore one should know that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s activities are different from others. The best policy is to follow the principles of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; that will make one perfect. It is also stated that there is no one who is master of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; everyone is His servant. Only K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is God, and everyone is servant. Everyone is complying with His order. There is no one who can deny His order. Everyone is acting according to His direction, being under His \nsuperintendence. As stated in the Brahm\xe2\x88\x92-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92, He is the cause of all causes.'
