My dear Arjuna, one who is engaged in My pure devotional service, free from the contaminations of previous activities and from mental speculation, who is \nfriendly to every living entity, certainly comes to Me.
PURPORTAnyone who wants to approach the Supreme of all the Personalities of Godhead, on the K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aaloka planet in the spiritual sky, and be intimately connected with the Supreme Personality, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, must take this formula, as is \nstated by the Supreme Himself. Therefore, this verse is considered to be the essence of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. The Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 is a book directed to the conditioned souls, who are engaged in the material world with the purpose of lording it over nature and who do not know of the real, spiritual life. The Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 is meant to show how one can understand his spiritual existence and his eternal relationship with the Supreme Spiritual Personality and to teach one how to go back home, back to Godhead. Now here is the verse \nwhich clearly explains the process by which one can attain success in his spiritual activity: devotional service. As far as work is concerned, one should transfer his energy entirely to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious activities. No work should be done by any man except in relationship to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. This called K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa-karma. One may be engaged in various activities, but one should not be attached to \nthe result of his work, but the result should be done for Him. For example, one may be engaged in business, but to transform that activity into K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa \nconsciousness, one has to do business for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. If K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the proprietor of '
b'the business, then K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa should enjoy the profit of the business. If a businessman is in possession of thousands and thousands of dollars, and if he has to offer all this to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, he can do it. This is work for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Instead of constructing a big building for his sense gratification, he can construct a nice temple for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and he can install the Deity of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and arrange for the Deity\xc3\x95s service, as is outlined in the authorized books of devotional service. This is all K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa-karma. One should not be attached to the result of his work, but the result should be offered to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. One should also accept as pras\xe2\x88\x92dam, food, the remnants of offerings to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. If, however, one is not able to construct a temple for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, one can engage himself in cleansing the temple of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; that is also K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa-karma. One can cultivate a garden. Anyone who has land\xc3\x91in India, at least, any poor man has a certain amount of land\xc3\x91can utilize that for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa by growing flowers to offer Him. He can sow tulas\xe2\x80\x9d plants because tulas\xe2\x80\x9d leaves are very important, and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has recommended this in \nBhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa desires that one offer Him either a leaf, or a flower, or a \nlittle water\xc3\x91and He is satisfied. This leaf especially refers to the tulas\xe2\x80\x9d So one can sow tulas\xe2\x80\x9d leaves and pour water on the plant. Thus, even the poorest man \ncan engage in the service of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. These are some of the examples of how one can engage in working for K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.The word mat-parama\xc5\xa1 refers to one who considers the association of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in His supreme abode to be the highest perfection of life. Such a person does not wish to be elevated to the higher planets such as the moon or sun or heavenly \nplanets, or even the highest planet of this universe, Brahmaloka. He has no attraction for that. He is only attracted to being transferred to the spiritual sky. And even in the spiritual sky he is not satisfied with merging into the glowing brahmajyoti effulgence, for he wants to enter the highest spiritual planet, namely K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aaloka, Goloka V\xe2\x80\x9end\xe2\x88\x92vana. He has full knowledge of that planet, and therefore he is not interested in any other. As indicated by the word mad-bhakta\xc5\xa1, he fully engages in devotional service, specifically in the \nnine processes of devotional engagement: hearing, chanting, remembering, worshiping, serving the lotus feet of the Lord, offering prayers, carrying out the orders of the Lord, making friends with Him, and surrendering everything to Him. One can engage in all nine devotional processes, or eight, or seven, or at least in one, and that will surely make one perfect.The term sa\xef\xac\x81ga-varjita\xc5\xa1 is very significant. One should disassociate himself from persons who are against K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Not only are the atheistic persons against '
b'K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, but also those who are attracted to fruitive activities and mental speculation. Therefore the pure form of devotional service is described in Bhakti-ras\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9eta-sindhu as follows: Gosv\xe2\x88\x92m\xe2\x80\x9d clearly states that if anyone wants to execute unalloyed devotional service, he must be freed from all kinds of material contamination. He must be freed from the association of persons who are addicted to fruitive activities and mental speculation. When, freed from such unwanted association and \nfrom the contamination of material desires, one favorably cultivates knowledge of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, that is called pure devotional service. . One should think of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and act for \nK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa favorably, not unfavorably. Ka\xe2\x80\xb9sa was an enemy of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s. From the very beginning of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s birth, he planned in so many ways to kill Him, and because he was always unsuccessful, he was always thinking of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Thus while working, while eating and while sleeping, he was always K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious \nin every respect, but that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness was not favorable, and therefore in spite of his always thinking of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa twenty-four hours a day, he was considered a demon, and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa at last killed him. Of course anyone who is killed by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa attains salvation immediately, but that is not the aim of the pure devotee. The pure devotee does not even want salvation. He does not want to be transferred even to the highest planet, Goloka V\xe2\x80\x9end\xe2\x88\x92vana. His only objective is to serve K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa wherever he may be.\nA devotee of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is friendly to everyone. Therefore it is said here that he has no enemy. How is this? A devotee situated in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness knows that only devotional service to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa can relieve a person from all the problems of life. He has personal experience of this, and therefore he wants to introduce this system, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, into human society. There are many examples in history of devotees of the Lord risking their lives for the spreading of God consciousness. The favorite example is Lord Jesus Christ. He \nwas crucified by the nondevotees, but He sacrificed His life for spreading God consciousness. Of course, it would be superficial to understand that He was killed. Similarly, in India also there are many examples, such as \xe2\x80\x93h\xe2\x88\x92kur Harid\xe2\x88\x92sa. Why such risk? Because they wanted to spread K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, and it is difficult. A K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa conscious person knows that if a man is suffering, it is due to his forgetfulness of his eternal relationship with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Therefore, the highest benefit one can render to human society is relieving one\xc3\x95s '
b'neighbor from all material problems. In such a way, a pure devotee is engaged in the service of the Lord. Now, we can imagine how merciful K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is to those engaged in His service, risking everything for Him. Therefore it is certain that such persons must reach the supreme planet after leaving the body.In summary, the universal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, which is a temporary manifestation, and the form of time which devours everything, and even the form of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, four-handed, have all been exhibited by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Thus K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the origin of all these manifestations. It is not that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is a manifestation of the original \nor Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the origin of all forms. There are hundreds and thousands of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aus, but for a devotee, no form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is important but the original form, two-handed \xe2\x80\xa1y\xe2\x88\x92masundara. In the Brahm\xe2\x88\x92-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 it is stated that those who are attached to the \xe2\x80\xa1y\xe2\x88\x92masundara form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in love and devotion can see Him always within the heart and cannot see anything else. One should understand, therefore, that the purport of this Eleventh Chapter is that the form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is essential and supreme.Thus end the Bhaktivedanta Purports to the Eleventh Chapter of the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 in the matter of the Universal Form.'
