he Supersoul, stays with him just to get him to return to the spiritual energy. The Lord is always eager to take him back to the spiritual energy, but due to his minute independence, the individual entity is \ncontinually rejecting the association of spiritual light. This misuse of '
b'independence is the cause of his material strife in the conditioned nature. The Lord, therefore, is always giving instruction from within and from without. From without He gives instructions as stated in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, and from within He tries to convince him that his activities in the material field are not conducive to real happiness. \xc3\x92Just give it up and turn your faith toward Me. Then you will be happy,\xc3\x93 He says. Thus the intelligent person who places his faith in the Param\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92 or the Supreme Personality of Godhead begins to advance toward a blissful eternal life of knowledge
