PURPORTHere the living entity is described as \xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x80\x9cvara, the controller of his own body. If he likes, he can change his body to a higher grade, and if he likes he can move to a lower class. Minute independence is there. The change his body undergoes depends upon him. At the time of death, the consciousness he has created will carry him on to the next type of body. If he has made his consciousness like that of a cat or dog, he is sure to change to a cat\xc3\x95s or dog\xc3\x95s body. And, if he has fixed his consciousness on godly qualities, he will change into the form of a demigod. And, if he is in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, he will be \ntransferred to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aaloka in the spiritual world and will associate with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. It is a false claim that after the annihilation of this body everything is finished. The individual soul is transmigrating from one body to another, and his present body and present activities are the background of his next body. One gets a different body according to karma, and he has to quit this body in due course. It is stated here that the subtle body, which carries the conception of the next body, develops another body in the next life. This process of \ntransmigrating from one body to another and struggling while in the body is called kar\xc5\x92ati or struggle for existence.'
