PURPORTAs already explained, the Lord in His incarnation as Vy\xe2\x88\x92sadeva compiled the Ved\xe2\x88\x92nta-sutra. Here the Lord is giving, in summary, the contents of the He says that the living entities, who are innumerable, can be divided into two classes\xc3\x91the fallible and the infallible. The living entities are eternally separated parts and parcels of the Supreme Personality of Godhead. When they are in contact with the material world, they are called and the Sanskrit words given here, mean that they are fallible. \nThose who are in oneness with the Supreme Personality of Godhead, however, are called infallible. Oneness does not mean that they have no individuality, \nbut that there is no disunity. They are all agreeable to the purpose of the creation. Of course, in the spiritual world, there is no such thing as creation, but since the Supreme Personality of Godhead has stated in the that He is the source of all emanations, that conception is explained.'
b'According to the statement of the Supreme Personality of Godhead, Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, there are two classes of men. The Vedas give evidence of this, so there is no doubt about it. The living entities, who are struggling in this world with the mind and five senses, have their material bodies which are changing as long as the living entities are conditioned. One\xc3\x95s body changes due to contact with matter; matter is changing, so the living entity appears to be changing. But in the spiritual world the body is not made of matter; therefore there is no change. In the material world the living entity undergoes six changes!birth, growth, duration, reproduction, then dwindling and vanishing. These are the changes of the material body. But in the spiritual world the body does not change; there is no old age, there is no birth, there is no death. There all exists in oneness. It is more clearly explained as any living entity who has come in contact with matter, beginning from the first created being, Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, down to a small ant, is changing its body; therefore they are all fallible. In the spiritual world, however, they are always liberated in oneness.
