b'the Supreme Personality of Godhead, \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, knows the purpose of the Vedas; no one else knows the purpose of the Vedas.The word bhajate is very significant. In many places the word bhajate is expressed in relationship with the service of the Supreme Lord. If a person is engaged in full K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness in devotional service of the Lord, it is to be understood that he has understood all the Vedic knowledge. In the Vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava parampar\xe2\x88\x92 it is said that if one is engaged in the devotional service of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, then there is no need for a spiritual process to understand the \nSupreme Absolute Truth. He has already come to the post because he is engaged in the devotional service of the Lord. He has ended all preliminary processes of understanding; similarly, if anyone, after speculating for hundreds of thousands of lives, does not come to the point that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead and that one has to surrender there, all his speculation for so many years and lives is a useless waste of time.
