b'daiva \xe2\x88\x92sura eva cadaivo vistara\xe2\x80\x9ca\xc5\xa1 prokta\xe2\x88\x92sura\xe2\x80\xb9 p\xe2\x88\x92rtha me \xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x80\x9e\xe2\x80\x9audvau\xc3\x91two; created living beings; loke\xc3\x91in this world; asmin\xc3\x91this; daiva\xc5\xa1\xc3\x91godly; \xe2\x88\x92sura\xc5\xa1\xc3\x91demoniac; eva\xc3\x91certainly; ca\xc3\x91and; daiva\xc5\xa1\xc3\x91divine; vistara\xe2\x80\x9ca\xc5\xa1\xc3\x91at great length; prokta\xc5\xa1\xc3\x91said; asuram\xc3\x91demoniac; p\xe2\x88\x92rtha\xc3\x91O son of P\xe2\x80\x9eth\xe2\x88\x92; me\xc3\x91from Me; \xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x80\x9e\xe2\x80\x9au\xc3\x91just hear.
TRANSLATION
O son of P\xe2\x80\x9eth\xe2\x88\x92, in this world there are two kinds of created beings. One is called the divine and the other demonic. I have already explained to you at \nlength the divine qualities. Now hear from Me of the demoniac.
PURPORTLord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, having assured Arjuna that he was born with the divine qualities, is now describing the demoniac way. The conditioned living entities are divided into two classes in this world. Those who are born with divine qualities follow a regulated life; that is to say they abide by the injunctions in scriptures and by the authorities. One should perform duties in the light of \nauthoritative scripture. This mentality is called divine. One who does not follow the regulative principles as they are laid down in the scriptures and who acts according to his whims is called demoniac or asuric. There is no other criterion but obedience to the regulative principles of scriptures. It is mentioned in Vedic literature that both the demigods and the demons are born of the Praj\xe2\x88\x92pati; the only difference is that one class obeys the Vedic injunctions and the other does not.
