PURPORTIn every civilized human society there is some set of scriptural rules and regulations which are followed from the beginning, especially among the \xe2\x80\xa2ryans, those who adopt the Vedic civilization and who are known as the most advanced civilized peoples. Those who do not follow the scriptural injunctions are supposed to be demons. Therefore it is stated here that the demons do not know the scriptural rules, nor do they have any inclination to follow them. Most of them do not know them, and even if some of them know, they have not the tendency to follow them. They have no faith, nor are they \nwilling to act in terms of the Vedic injunctions. The demons are not clean, either externally or internally.One should always be careful to keep his body clean by bathing, brushing teeth, changing clothes, etc. As far as internal cleanliness is concerned, one should always remember the holy names of God and chant Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, Hare K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, Hare Hare/Hare R\xe2\x88\x92ma, Hare R\xe2\x88\x92ma, R\xe2\x88\x92ma R\xe2\x88\x92ma, Hare Hare. The demons neither like nor follow all these rules for external and \ninternal cleanliness.As for behavior, there are many rules and regulations guiding human behavior, such as the Manu-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92, which is the law of the human race. Even up to today, those who are Hindu follow the Manu-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92. Laws of inheritance and other legalities are derived from this book. Now, in the Manu-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92, it is '
b'clearly stated that a woman should not be given freedom. That does not mean that women are to be kept as slaves, but they are like children. Children are not given freedom, but that does not mean that they are kept as slaves. The demons have now neglected such injunctions, and they think that women should be given as much freedom as men. However, this has not improved the social condition of the world. Actually, a woman should be given protection at every stage of life. She should be given protection by the father in her younger days, by the husband in her youth, and by the grownup sons in her old age. \nThis is proper social behavior according to the Manu-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92. But modern education has artificially devised a puffed up concept of womanly life, and therefore marriage is practically now an imagination in human society. Nor is the moral condition of woman very good now. The demons, therefore, do not accept any instruction which is good for society, and because they do not follow the experience of great sages and the rules and regulations laid down by the sages, the social condition of the demoniac people is very miserable.
